description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Community Mental Health Nurse who is caring, compassionate, hardworking and driven in ensuring that our services users and their families receive the highest standards of care. We are looking for someone who is passionate about psychosis and able to deliver evidence based interventions in the community to continually improve care and to ensure service users have the best possible experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting to a Band 5 Nursing post in the Psychosis Pathway, Shropshire West Team. This area covers Shrewsbury, Oswestry, Ludlow and surrounding areas; however the post will be predominatly working in the Ludlow / Shrewsbury areas. The successful post holder would act as a Care Coordinator to a group of clients with psychosis, be expected to work closely with the MDT in ensuring recovery focused care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal discussion about the postplease contact Brogan Browett (Pathway Manager) or Terri Greenhalgh (Quality Lead) on 03003033426.&lt;/p&gt;
